<plot>Stone Mountain, Georgia, is famous for its Mount Rushmore-like carving of Confederate Civil War leaders. Less famous is the mountain's history as a symbol of racism and its transformation into an amusement park. "Stone Mountain" is a short documentary film that explores Southern history with a trip to one of its most popular attractions.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?516370</url></doc>
